<div class="entry" id="post3700">
   <h3 class="entry-header"><a href="http://blogs.roanoke.com/theedge/2013/09/24/travel-abroad-summer-2013-patrick-henry-colombia/">On top of the world: Local students travel abroad</a></h3>        <div class="contents_body">
        <div class="entry-body">
            <p><a href="http://blogs.roanoke.com/theedge/files/2013/09/edgeglobe0925.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-3774" alt="edgeglobe0925" src="http://blogs.roanoke.com/theedge/files/2013/09/edgeglobe0925-300x300.jpg" width="300" height="300" /></a>Several schools in the Roanoke area participated in international trips over the past six months. The various benefits of school-sponsored travel-abroad trips include language acquisition, the cultural perspective gained, or simply great experiences.</p>
<p>Grace Casola, a first year at University of Virginia and a participant in the Patrick Henry-Colombia exchange said, &#8220;I think it is important to take advantage of your teenage years to travel while your mind is still relatively open to new things. School sponsored travel abroad is a great way to extend your horizons in not only a geographical way, but also a mental way (many of the trips have educational components that are unparalleled in solo travel).&#8221;</p>
<p>In addition to Patrick Henry&#8217;s exchange with Colombia, other local students spent time in Paris, London, Spain and Scotland.</p>
<p><strong>Patrick Henry-Colombia exchange</strong><br />
<strong>By: Ciara Mulcahy and Patrick Elder, Patrick Henry High School</strong></p>
<p>In June a group of nine Patrick Henry High School students spent three weeks with host families in Colombia, South America. These Colombian hosts weren&#8217;t strangers to the Patrick Henry exchange students as they had spent three weeks attending Patrick Henry in February. Alec Paget, a freshman at University of Virginia and Patrick Henry graduate, commented on the Colombian students’ impressions of Roanoke.</p>
<p>He said, “They seemed extremely impressed and surprised by many things about the United States, especially how large our high school is and the amount of traveling we do by car in general.”</p>
<p>Joe Jamison, a current senior at Patrick Henry High school, elaborated. Jamison said, “The Colombians seemed shocked that we lived in isolated houses, with our own yards. In Colombia, the city of Chinchina that we stayed in had a population of about 90,000 people, just less than that of Roanoke, but the area it encompassed was much, much smaller.”</p>
<p>This cultural opportunity was organized by Senora Beatriz Ponton, a native Colombian and Spanish teacher at Patrick Henry. A great experience seems to have been had by all.</p>
<p>Padget said, “We were basically immersed in the culture of Colombia for three weeks, which included eating a lot of tasty Colombian food, going to various cities, and dancing salsa and bachata, just to name a few experiences.”</p>
<p>The students have remained mindful of their time spent in Colombia, as evident in their Facebook wallpapers and profile pictures.</p>
<p>Jamison added, “I have maintained almost a constant conversation over Facebook with my host, Sebastian, since I got back to America, as well as shorter conversations with other Colombians.”</p>
<p><object width="400" height="300"> <param name="flashvars" value="offsite=true&lang=en-us&page_show_url=%2Fphotos%2F99941179%40N04%2Fsets%2F72157635571319835%2Fshow%2Fwith%2F9736622119%2F&page_show_back_url=%2Fphotos%2F99941179%40N04%2Fsets%2F72157635571319835%2Fwith%2F9736622119%2F&set_id=72157635571319835&jump_to=9736622119"></param> <param name="movie" value="http://www.flickr.com/apps/slideshow/show.swf?v=124984"></param> <param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" src="http://www.flickr.com/apps/slideshow/show.swf?v=124984" allowFullScreen="true" flashvars="offsite=true&lang=en-us&page_show_url=%2Fphotos%2F99941179%40N04%2Fsets%2F72157635571319835%2Fshow%2Fwith%2F9736622119%2F&page_show_back_url=%2Fphotos%2F99941179%40N04%2Fsets%2F72157635571319835%2Fwith%2F9736622119%2F&set_id=72157635571319835&jump_to=9736622119" width="400" height="300"></embed></object></p>
<p><strong>Lord Botetourt students travel to Paris and London</strong><br />
<strong>By: Kelsie Graybill, Lord Botetourt High School</strong></p>
<p>This past April Lord Botetourt High School students traveled to Paris and London. Lynne Bolton, a history teacher at the school, was the trip leader. Bolton explained that the group met with a tour guide that showed them many the fun and educational parts of the cities. The group learned history, went sight-seeing, and had a blast together.</p>
<p>Bolton and student Rachel Overbay agreed that one of the best parts of the trip was experiencing different cultures.</p>
<p>When Bolton was asked what her favorite part was she responded, “From the time we arrived to the time we left.”</p>
<p>She said that she firmly believes that everyone should visit other lands to experience other cultures if they have the chance.</p>
<p>Another trip is planned this June to Italy.</p>
<p><object width="400" height="300"> <param name="flashvars" value="offsite=true&lang=en-us&page_show_url=%2Fphotos%2F99941179%40N04%2Fsets%2F72157635670293526%2Fshow%2Fwith%2F9791740936%2F&page_show_back_url=%2Fphotos%2F99941179%40N04%2Fsets%2F72157635670293526%2Fwith%2F9791740936%2F&set_id=72157635670293526&jump_to=9791740936"></param> <param name="movie" value="http://www.flickr.com/apps/slideshow/show.swf?v=124984"></param> <param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" src="http://www.flickr.com/apps/slideshow/show.swf?v=124984" allowFullScreen="true" flashvars="offsite=true&lang=en-us&page_show_url=%2Fphotos%2F99941179%40N04%2Fsets%2F72157635670293526%2Fshow%2Fwith%2F9791740936%2F&page_show_back_url=%2Fphotos%2F99941179%40N04%2Fsets%2F72157635670293526%2Fwith%2F9791740936%2F&set_id=72157635670293526&jump_to=9791740936" width="400" height="300"></embed></object></p>
<p><strong>Cave Spring student spends summer abroad</strong><br />
<strong>By: Roshni Lalchandani, Cave Spring High School</strong></p>
<p align="LEFT">Many students around the valley traveled to new and exciting places over the summer, and Cave Spring High School junior Sarah Clark had adventures she was glad to share. From Paris, France to London, England to Edinburgh, Scotland, Clark’s summer was definitely one to remember.</p>
<p align="LEFT">Clark began 21 days of travel in July with Education First Tours. After 11 days Clark’s mother, Bonnie, was able to join Sarah and they revisited some of the same cities.</p>
<p align="LEFT">After visiting London with her choir on a previous trip, Clark knew she definitely wanted to go back. Paris was on the list after she studied French for three years in school.</p>
<p align="LEFT">&#8220;Traveling abroad is absolutely incredible, and everyone should be able to experience it at least once in their lifetime,&#8221; she said.</p>
<p><strong>North Cross students travel to Spain</strong><br />
<strong>By: Blair Thurman and Mehreen Imam, North Cross School</strong></p>
<p>Most students’ summers are spent working or traveling with family, but for some students from North Cross School the summer was filled with a two-week trip to Spain. The trip was sponsored by North Cross’ Global Studies Program and was a immersion trip for the students. The students stayed for a one week in Ronda, then traveled to the eastern coast of Spain. They also visited Granada, Aguilas, San Pedro, Madrid, Albacete and Cartagena.</p>
<p>While in Spain, the students stayed with host families.  Ann Ickes, a senior at North Cross, commented that during when the students were not in school the host families would take them around Spain, walk around the town, and go to the homes of friends and family.</p>
<p>“I really do miss them. We were always laughing and it has given me memories and stories that I will never forget,” said Ickes.</p>
<div class="printfriendly pf-alignleft"><a href="http://www.printfriendly.com/print?url=http://blogs.roanoke.com/theedge/2013/09/24/travel-abroad-summer-2013-patrick-henry-colombia/" rel="nofollow" onclick="window.print(); return false;"><img style="border:none;-webkit-box-shadow:none; box-shadow:none;" src="http://cdn.printfriendly.com/pf-button.gif" alt="Print Friendly" /></a></div>                    </div>
